%I A395670 #17 May 07 2026 00:19:50
%S A395670 24,7296,38016,432000,1199232,4838784,728136864,2317867776,2917012608
%N A395670 Integers x>0 such that there exists an integer y>0 such that sigma(x)*psi(x) = x^2 + y^2.
%C A395670 The numbers x and y form a sigma*psi-quadratic pair.
%C A395670 a(9) <= 2917012608. If 864 | a(9) then a(9) = 2917012608. - _David A. Corneth_, May 03 2026
%H A395670 S. I. Dimitrov, <a href="https://hal.science/hal-05303937">On σψ-quadratic k-tuples and related generalizations</a>, hal-05303937, 2025.
%e A395670 24 is a term since sigma(24) * psi(24) = 60 * 48 = 24^2 + 48^2.
%o A395670 (PARI) isok(k) = {my(f = factor(k), d = sigma(f) * prod(i=1, #f~, (f[i, 1]+1) * f[i, 1]^(f[i, 2]-1)) - k^2); d > 0 && issquare(d);} \\ _Amiram Eldar_, May 03 2026
%Y A395670 Cf. A000203, A001481, A001615, A066784.
%K A395670 nonn,hard,more,new
%O A395670 1,1
%A A395670 _S. I. Dimitrov_, May 03 2026
%E A395670 a(8) added and a(9) verified by _Amiram Eldar_, May 03 2026
